moves.1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Nf6 4. Nc3: ?! I believe this is an inaccuracy, because my opinion is that Black is quite happy with the exchanges happening in the game.
moves.4... Nxe4 5. Bxf7+: Probably better than the straightforward Nxe4, at least he makes my King a little bit exposed.
moves.5... Kxf7 6. Nxe4 d5 7. Neg5+ Kg8 8. d3: I played this move after a long thought, but in the end I evaluated that my center strike would have come first.
moves.12... e3:
! Generally I'm a quiet, positional player, but I felt like this move couldn't be bad, and I was really happy to see variation confirmed that.
In general, it is usually good to open the enemy King at the cost of a pawn, especially if you can get so many pieces active with gain of some tempi.
moves.13. fxe3 Qh4+ 14. Kf1: I don't like this, I believe Ke2 would have been more resistant.
moves.14... Qxh3+ 15. Kg1 Bc5: Another piece comes in with gain of a tempo, and defense is quite difficult now.
moves.16. Qf3: ?? The final mistake, Nc4 or Nf1 would have prolonged the game more.
moves.16... Bxe3+: ! This final blow nicely closes the game, because White loses his Queen by force.
